
Overview of noun salvation

The noun salvation has 4 senses (first 2 from tagged texts)
                                      
1. (10) redemption, salvation -- ((theology) the act of delivering from sin or saving from evil)
2. (1) salvation -- (a means of preserving from harm or unpleasantness; "tourism was their economic salvation"; "they turned to individualism as their salvation")
3. salvation -- (the state of being saved or preserved from harm)
4. salvation -- (saving someone or something from harm or from an unpleasant situation; "the salvation of his party was the president's major concern")
